# Sūra LI.: Zāriyāt, or the Winds That Scatter.

### Section 1

![](../gif/051/051_001.gif)

1. Wa**al**<u>ththa</u>riy<u>a</u>ti <u>th</u>arw<u>a</u>**n**

1\. By the (Winds)  
That scatter broadcast;

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/051/051_002.gif)

2. Fa**a**l<u>ha</u>mil<u>a</u>ti wiqr<u>a</u>**n**

2\. And those that  
Lift and bear away  
Heavy weights;

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/051/051_003.gif)

3. Fa**a**lj<u>a</u>riy<u>a</u>ti yusr<u>a</u>**n**

3\. And those that  
Flow with ease  
And gentleness;

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/051/051_004.gif)

4. Fa**a**lmuqassim<u>a</u>ti amr<u>a</u>**n**

4\. And those that  
Distribute and apportion  
By Command;—

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/051/051_005.gif)

5. Innam<u>a</u> tooAAadoona la<u>sa</u>diq**un**

5\. Verily that which ye  
Are promised is true;

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/051/051_006.gif)

6. Wa-inna a**l**ddeena law<u>a</u>qiAA**un**

6\. And verily Judgment  
And Justice must  
Indeed come to pass.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/051/051_007.gif)

7. Wa**al**ssam<u>a</u>-i <u>tha</u>ti al<u>h</u>ubuk**i**

7\. By the Sky  
With (its) numerous Paths,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/051/051_008.gif)

8. Innakum lafee qawlin mukhtalif**in**

8\. Truly ye are in  
A doctrine discordant,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/051/051_009.gif)

9. Yu/faku AAanhu man ofik**a**

9\. Through which are deluded (away  
From the Truth) such  
As would be deluded.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/051/051_010.gif)

10. Qutila alkharr<u>as</u>oon**a**

10\. Woe to the falsehood-mongers,—

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/051/051_011.gif)

11. Alla<u>th</u>eena hum fee ghamratin s<u>a</u>hoon**a**

11\. Those who (flounder) heedless  
In a flood of confusion:

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/051/051_012.gif)

12. Yas-aloona ayy<u>a</u>na yawmu a**l**ddeen**i**

12\. They ask, "When will be  
The Day of Judgment  
And Justice?"

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/051/051_013.gif)

13. Yawma hum AAal<u>a</u> a**l**nn<u>a</u>ri yuftanoon**a**

13\. (It will be) a Day  
When they will be tried  
(And tested) over the Fire!

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/051/051_014.gif)

14. <u>Th</u>ooqoo fitnatakum h<u>atha</u> alla<u>th</u>ee kuntum bihi
tastaAAjiloon**a**

14\. "Taste ye your trial!  
This is what ye used  
To ask to be hastened!

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/051/051_015.gif)

15. Inna almuttaqeena fee jann<u>a</u>tin waAAuyoon**in**

15\. As to the Righteous,  
They will be in the midst  
Of Gardens and Springs,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/051/051_016.gif)

16. <u>A</u>khi<u>th</u>eena m<u>a</u> <u>a</u>t<u>a</u>hum rabbuhum
innahum k<u>a</u>noo qabla <u>tha</u>lika mu<u>h</u>sineen**a**

16\. Taking joy in the things  
Which their Lord gives them,  
Because, before then, they  
Lived a good life.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/051/051_017.gif)

17. K<u>a</u>noo qaleelan mina allayli m<u>a</u> yahjaAAoon**a**

17\. They were in the habit  
Of sleeping but little  
By night,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/051/051_018.gif)

18. Wabi**a**l-as<u>ha</u>ri hum yastaghfiroon**a**

18\. And in the hours  
Of early dawn,  
They (were found) praying  
For Forgiveness;

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/051/051_019.gif)

19. Wafee amw<u>a</u>lihim <u>h</u>aqqun li**l**ss<u>a</u>-ili
wa**a**lma<u>h</u>room**i**

19\. And in their wealth  
And possessions (was remembered)  
The right of the (needy,)  
Him who asked, and him  
Who (for some reason) was  
Prevented (from asking).

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/051/051_020.gif)

20. Wafee al-ar<u>d</u>i <u>a</u>y<u>a</u>tun lilmooqineen**a**

20\. On the earth  
Are Signs for those  
Of assured Faith,

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/051/051_021.gif)

21. Wafee anfusikum afal<u>a</u> tub<u>s</u>iroon**a**

21\. As also in your, own  
Selves: will ye not  
Then see?

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/051/051_022.gif)

22. Wafee a**l**ssam<u>a</u>-i rizqukum wam<u>a</u> tooAAadoon**a**

22\. And in heaven is  
Your Sustenance, as (also)  
That which ye are promised.

------------------------------------------------------------------------

![](../gif/051/051_023.gif)

23. Fawarabbi a**l**ssam<u>a</u>-i wa**a**l-ar<u>d</u>i innahu
la<u>h</u>aqqun mithla m<u>a</u> annakum tan<u>t</u>iqoon**a**

23\. Then, by the Lord  
Of heaven and earth,  
This is the very Truth,  
As much as the fact  
That ye can speak  
Intelligently to each other.

